SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: Identifying biovar name of the biological challenge agent.
A general classification of the biological challenge agent used in the study.

SKOS_CONCEPT.alt_label: Biological Agent Certificate of Analysis Indicator;Biological Agent CoA Indicator
SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: An indication as to whether a certificate of analysis exists for the biological challenge agent.
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: Biological Agent Certificate of Analysis Indicator

SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: An indication as to whether the biological challenge agent is engineered rather than naturally occurring.
The genus and species of the biological challenge agent used in the study.

SKOS_CONCEPT.alt_label: Bio Master Bank or Seed Stock Dir Supp;Bio Master Bank or Seed Stock Direct Supplier
SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: The name of the direct supplier of the master bank or seed stock of organisms from which the biological challenge agent came.
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: Master Bank or Seed Stock Immediate Supplier

SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: The unique identifier code assigned by the manufacturer or distributor to a specific quantity of biological challenge agent. This may include batch number, lot number, spore lot number, batch/lot number, etc.

SKOS_CONCEPT.alt_label: Biological Agent Nucleotide Sequence Ind;Biological Agent Nucleotide Sequence Indicator
SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: An indication as to whether the genetic sequence of the biological challenge agent has been determined.

SKOS_CONCEPT.alt_label: Biological Agent Nucleotide Sequence Loc;Biological Agent Nucleotide Sequence Location
SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: The reference, citation, or database location of the nucleotide sequence for the biological challenge agent.
Identifying serovar name of the biological challenge agent.
Identifying strain name of the biological challenge agent.

A description of the area or extent of the body that is exposed to radiation, which may include information about the body part that is irradiated and procedures that may be done in conjunction with the radiation.

SKOS_CONCEPT.alt_label: Bio Ag Work Bank/Primary Stock Char Ind;Biological Working Bank or Primary Stock Characterized Indicator
SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: An indication as to whether the primary molecular and biological characteristics of the working bank or primary stock were confirmed.
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: Working Bank or Primary Stock Characterized Indicator

SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: A general classification of the challenge agent used in the study.
The geographic location of the person, company, organization, or institution that supplied the challenge agent used in the study.
The name of the person, company, organization, or institution that supplied the challenge agent used in the study.
The unique numerical identifier assigned by the Chemical Abstract Service (CAS), a division of the American Chemical Society, to the chemical challenge agent used in the study.
The name of the chemical challenge agent used in the study.

SKOS_CONCEPT.alt_label: Chemical Ag Metabolite Causes Injury Ind;Chemical Agent Metabolite Causes Injury Indicator
SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: An indication as to whether a metabolite of the chemical challenge agent is known to cause or contribute to the injury or condition of interest.
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: Challenge Agent Metabolite Caused Injury Indicator

SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: An indication as to whether a certificate of analysis exists for the chemical challenge agent.
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: Chemical Agent Certificate of Analysis Indicator

SKOS_CONCEPT.alt_label: Chemical Agent Material Ident Code;Chemical Agent Material Identification Code
SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: The unique identifier code assigned by the manufacturer or distributor to a specific quantity of chemical challenge agent. This may include batch number, lot number, batch/lot number, etc.

SKOS_CONCEPT.alt_label: Combined Injury (Rad and Non-Rad) Ind;Combined Injury (Radiation and Non-Radiation) Indicator
SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: An indication as to whether the radiation injury is combined with infectious, physical, thermal, and/or chemical trauma.

SKOS_CONCEPT.alt_label: Exp Onset of Rad/Nuc Targeted Injury;Expected Onset of Rad/Nuc Targeted Injury
SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: The relative timing of the expected onset of the targeted injury, with respect to radiation exposure.
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: Expected Onset of Rad/Nuc Targeted Injury

SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: A description of the irradiation field as it pertains to orientation to the body and, when appropriate, the sequencing of exposure(s).

SKOS_CONCEPT.alt_label: Multiple Challenge Agent Category Ind;Multiple Challenge Agent Category Indicator
SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: An indication as to whether the animal was challenged with agents from more than one challenge agent category.
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: Multiple Challenge Agent Different Category Indicator

SKOS_CONCEPT.alt_label: Multiple Challenge Agent Same Cat Ind;Multiple Challenge Agent Same Category Indicator
SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: An indication as to whether the animal was challenged with more than one agent from a single challenge agent category.
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: Multiple Challenge Agent Same Category Indicator

SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: The proportion of bone marrow that is not irradiated, i.e., shielded or removed from field.
The form of ionizing radiation that is emitted by the rad/nuc agent source.

SKOS_CONCEPT.alt_label: Rad/Nuc Agent Irrad Source Beam Strength;Rad/Nuc Agent Irradiation Source Beam Strength
SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: The energy of the irradiation beam produced by the source.
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: Radiological/Nuclear Agent Irradiation Source Beam Strength

SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: An indication as to whether there is more than one type of ionizing radiation associated with the rad/nuc challenge.
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: Challenge Agent Type Mixed Field Indicator

SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: The literal identifier of the radioisotope, specified as the symbol of the chemical element followed by the mass number.
The mode by which the radiological or nuclear challenge agent is delivered to the subject.
The type of radiation injury that is being induced in the animal.
